  "text": "RNase protection assays were used to assay quantitatively the changes in the levels of NMDA receptor subunit transcripts NR1, NR2B, and NR2A. Quantitative Western blotting of protein from colliculi of the same age that used antibodies specific for NR1, NR2B, and NR2A were used to measure levels of the corresponding proteins. Time points were chosen for ease of comparison with previous anatomical , molecular [CITATION_1] , and biochemical [CITATION_2] results in this same neuropil. To assure accurate comparisons with the previous studies and the current physiological assays of synaptic f unction, we took great care to dissect out only the superficial visual layers of the superior colliculus for these analyses.",
